Class Animation

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.circle.animation.Animation

    public class Animation
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable

    • Constructor Detail

      • Animation

        public Animation(java.lang.String name,
                 java.awt.Image image,
                 int numOfFrames,
                 int frameWidth)
        Creates a new Animation using the Strip animation format. This assumes that the Animation is all in a single row
        Parameters:
        name - Name of the Animation
        image - The BufferedImage that contains every frame of the animation is strip format
        numOfFrames - Defines how many frames are in the Animation
        frameWidth - Defines the width of each frame of the Animation

      • Animation

        public Animation(java.lang.String name,
                 java.awt.Image image,
                 int numOfFrames,
                 int framesAcross,
                 int frameWidth,
                 int frameHeight,
                 boolean spriteSheet)
        Creates a new Animation using the Sprite Sheet animation format. This assumes that the Animation is broken up into separate rows and columns. This can also be used for Strip Format Animations
        Parameters:
        name - Name of the Animation
        image - The BufferedImage that contains every frame of the animation is strip format
        numOfFrames - Defines how many frames are in the Animation
        framesAcross - Number of frames in each Row
        frameWidth - Defines the width of each frame of the Animation
        frameHeight - Defines the height of each frame of the Animation
        spriteSheet - Defines if the Animation type is Sprite Sheet. Setting to false will load as Strip Format
